description._content: Title: [Paul Raigorodsky, Leda Raigorodsky Wedding] Creator: Richie, Robert Yarnall, 1908-1984 Date: February 4, 1949 Part Of: Robert Yarnall Richie photograph collection Place: Austin, Texas Description: Paul Raigorodsky standing in front of a portrait at the wedding of his daughter, Leda Raigorodsky. Paul M. Raigorodsky testified before Mr. Albert E. Jenner, Jr., assistant counsel of the President's Commission (the Warren Commission) on March 31, 1964. His testimony described his relationship with George De Mohrenschildt, a friend and associate of Lee Harvey Oswald. Physical Description: 1 negative film: black and white; 6 x 6 cm File Name: ag1982_0234_3088_42_raigorodsky_wedding_sm_opt.jpg Rights: Please cite Southern Methodist University, Central University Libraries, DeGolyer Library when using this image file. A high-quality version of this file may be obtained for a fee by contacting degolyer@smu.edu.
